President of Liberia, George Weah has declared the university of Liberia and all other public universities in Liberia tuition free. He took to his Facebook page to announced the news few minutes ago.


The announcement generated lots of joy as thousands of Africans spoke good about the one time football star.

National Daily monitored the comments and discovered many Nigerians using the opportunity to condemn the present administration while they praised the Liberian president.

Here is the Facebook Link:

https://m.facebook.com/story.php?story_fbid=1088424534652473&id=227044367457165&fs=0&focus_composer=0





“Today,  I’m excited to announce that I have declared the University of Liberia and all other Public Universities in Liberia  tuition free for all undergraduates”















